  "text": "Table four presents the partial correlations in which gender and age were controlled, following the suggestion of [CITATION_1] . From this table it can be demonstrated that when sex and age were controlled the negative relationships between honesty/humility and belief in superstitions (r= -.20, p=.030), and between honesty/humility and precognition (r= -.24, p=.008) were maintained. Further, a negative relationship was demonstrated between openness and belief in superstitions (r= -.25, p=.007) and between openness and belief in precognition (r= -.18, p=.05). After controlling for age and gender the correlation between conscientiousness and belief in superstitions was negated.",
